tsnav.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Ratsnav</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br>  Posts: 1<br> <font color=#A62A2A>(9/21/02 11:47:33 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub94.ezboard.com/ffirionaviefrm1.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=2769.topic>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Question for the kitties</span><hr size=1> I am thinking of starting up a shaman on the moon.  Is money easier to come by starting out than it was when Luclin first came out?  Don't get me wrong, I don't twink, I just like to be able to get my spells in a somewhat timely manner.  Any responses are greatly appreciated!<br>
<br>
<br>
Soon to be Vah Shir shaman <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=d1c3b5><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub94.ezboard.com/ulethecerulre.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Lethe Cerulre</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Siokitty Silvermoon <br>Krazy Kitty</span><br>  Posts: 170<br> <font color=#A62A2A>(9/21/02 4:28:13 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub94.ezboard.com/ffirionaviefrm1.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=2769.topic&index=1>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Question for the kitties</span><hr size=1> Not really, but the thing you need to know is that the most part of the beginning of a young Vah Shir Shaman's adventures is getting yourself set for the beginning of the Sonic Bane quest.  If I remember correctly there aren't any specific newbie armor quests... there's a few that I remember and are pretty easy.  Once you get to the right level I know you can get some items and sell them off and high prices to people.  I never really had too much of a problem with getting my spells.  Contact me in game if you want to ask any questions.<br>
<br>
Siokitty <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=d1c3b5><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub94.ezboard.com/uratsnav.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Ratsnav</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br>  Posts: 2<br> <font color=#A62A2A>(9/21/02 5:00:43 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub94.ezboard.com/ffirionaviefrm1.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=2769.topic&index=2>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Question for the kitties</span><hr size=1> I figured as much, just hoped that Verant had placed some drops in like in the Freeport area.<br>
<br>
So what is the Sonic Bane quest?  I tried to do some research on it but came up with nothing. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=d1c3b5><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub94.ezboard.com/ustrayvz.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Stray VZ</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br>  Posts: 18<br> <font color=#A62A2A>(9/21/02 6:11:29 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub94.ezboard.com/ffirionaviefrm1.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=2769.topic&index=3>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Question for the kitties</span><hr size=1> Theres a guard at the south gate named Khala Dun Aeora that tips off a quest that includes giving scorpian venom sacks (of scorpians in the crater L2-3) to a guy named Spiritist Ragnar.He in turn gives you a piece of padded armor and several silver for each sack..you can in turn sell them back to him for several gp each. Good way to get cash and armor for a newbie.<br>
<br>
For some reaso that same guy also buys stuff for alot higher then other merchants...so go to him to sell if you must.<br>
<br>
Say Hi to Khin if you happen to pass him. <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START ;) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/wink.gif ALT=";)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END-->  <p></p><i>Edited by: <A HREF=http://pub94.ezboard.com/ustrayvz.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Stray VZ</A> at: 9/21/02 6:12:12 pm<br></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=d1c3b5><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub94.ezboard.com/uthevolcanogod.showPublicProfile?language=EN>thevolcanogod</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br>  Posts: 70<br> <font color=#A62A2A>(9/23/02 3:24:33 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub94.ezboard.com/ffirionaviefrm1.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=2769.topic&index=4>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Question for the kitties</span><hr size=1> OMG the money situation is awful for Vah Shir Shamans. I am now lvl 30 and have just saved up about 100PP past the purchase of all of my spells to equip myself with. I am still wearing mostly Loda Kai and Bandit armor with that lucky Sambata Warhammer I got for 20PP. Of course I have been spending my time fighting and leveling rather than Silk or Bone Chip farming, but there is so little in the way of money loot in the Shar Vahl and Shadeweaver newbie zones it will make you cry. I spent one night killing skeletal hunters for rusty weapons to buy my SOW spell at level 9 because there was no way I could make the Paludal death run at that level to go to greener pastures.<br>
<br>
If you need money get off the moon and into The Warrens, Butcherblock (Aqua Goblins), and later, Stonebrunt Mountains (all of the cats drop LQ, MQ or HQ pelts).<br>
<br>
The sonic bane quest is fun but takes a while and you will need some money to raise some trade skills (which you won't have anyways). I am just at the point before you have to do the class-specific quests so pretty soon I will have to try and find other Vah Shir who are at that stage and trade some items.<br>
Any questions about starting out, please contact me.<br>
Vulrath Vadrigaar<br>
30 Vah Shir Shaman *the hard way*<br>
Wolves of Antonica <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=d1c3b5><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title><A HREF="http://www.ezboard.com/promotions/csc.html" TARGET="_blank" ><IMG SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/image/cscicon.gif" WIDTH="20" HEIGHT="20" BORDER="0" align="absmiddle"></A> <A HREF=http://pub94.ezboard.com/unahide.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Nahide</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br>  Posts: 189<br> <font color=#A62A2A>(9/23/02 6:08:46 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub94.ezboard.com/ffirionaviefrm1.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=2769.topic&index=5>Reply</a>    <br>ezSupporter<br> <BR><img src=http://www.datasync.com/~jrocker/pictures/bigglesworth.jpg WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Question for the kitties</span><hr size=1> I can make the warrior part of the sonic wolf bane weapon, I still have all the stuff, just need the ore that drops in hollowshade.<br>
