 <p><b><a href=http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=53989>Nahide' Altaica , Khala Dun Journeycat Myrmidon of the 56th rank</a><br><a href=http://pub94.ezboard.com/bfirionavie>
Firiona Vie Server</a><br>
Proud Officer of <a href=http://www.ebonstorm.com/>Ebon Storm</a></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=d1c3b5><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub94.ezboard.com/ucobra102.showPublicProfile?language=EN>cobra102</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br>  Posts: 46<br> <font color=#A62A2A>(9/23/02 11:35:10 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub94.ezboard.com/ffirionaviefrm1.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=2769.topic&index=6>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Question for the kitties</span><hr size=1> The money situation is not that bad once you can hunt Grimlings (Acrylia drops) and Owlbears (Perfect Owlbear Pelt) and they are ok exp.<br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE BOLD START--><b> Being a Vah Shir is not about getting a port to Norrath at level 3 and pretending you are an elf or human with a tail.</b><!--EZCODE BOLD END--> <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=d1c3b5><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub94.ezboard.com/urhatha.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Rhatha</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Animist of Shar Vahl<br>The Dark Side wants YOU!</span><br>  Posts: 426<br> <font color=#A62A2A>(9/24/02 12:11:52 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub94.ezboard.com/ffirionaviefrm1.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=2769.topic&index=7>Reply</a>   <BR><img src=http://darklance.freewebspace.com/images/rhatha.jpg WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Question for the kitties</span><hr size=1> Eh.  There is little to no money at early levels, that's part of life on Luclin.  Once you can handle Pal bandit camps (if you manage to avoid the idiots) and Neth Lair, it gets a tad batter. <p>-----------------------------<BR><A HREF='http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=112438' target=new>Rhatha Sha`Naya</A> and Swiftclaw <Ebon Storm><BR>
56th season Khati Sha and Warder<BR>
Firiona Vie<BR>
<A HREF='http://darklance.freewebspace.com/index.html'>Rhatha's Lair</A><BR>
<I>Nothing is going to stop me now.</I></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=d1c3b5><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub94.ezboard.com/uthevolcanogod.showPublicProfile?language=EN>thevolcanogod</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br>  Posts: 71<br> <font color=#A62A2A>(9/24/02 8:41:31 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub94.ezboard.com/ffirionaviefrm1.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=2769.topic&index=8>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Question for the kitties</span><hr size=1> I really could care less about specifically hunting on Norrath or any other race Cobra. What I care about is not having enough money to buy my cool spells that I have earned the right to cast because VI decided Vah Shir newbies don't need money.<br>
<br>
If you think being a Vah Shir is about being completely poor and frustrated for 30 levels then by all means stay on the moon. If you would actually like the fun of casting spells at your current level and seeing your toon get equipped in some moderately decent armor then see my above post for money options. Just don't give me BS about it not &quot;being the Vah Shir way&quot; to go and hunt anywhere else but Luclin.<br>
<br>
Recondites are some decent loot for the teens, but not great. The weapons they drop are mostly garbage and they drop some armor occasionally which you can use, but not often, and the money loot is OK - maybe 1PP and change on some of the tougher condies. BUT you could make a lot more a lot quicker elsewere.<br>
<br>
The gimlings that drop Acryla and the Owlbears that drop Perfect pelts aren't anywhere near to being in the range of killable by a newbie.<br>
Vulrath <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=d1c3b5><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub94.ezboard.com/ustrayvz.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Stray VZ</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br>  Posts: 22<br> <font color=#A62A2A>(9/24/02 9:44:08 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub94.ezboard.com/ffirionaviefrm1.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=2769.topic&index=9>Reply</a>   <BR><img src=http://www.planetnintendo.com/ff1/graphics/gaia/ani/pirate.gif WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Question for the kitties</span><hr size=1>  Hitting old ladies on the head and running off with their purses works too. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=d1c3b5><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub94.ezboard.com/uscorchedscales.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Scorchedscales</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br>  Posts: 13<br> <font color=#A62A2A>(9/24/02 9:59:54 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub94.ezboard.com/ffirionaviefrm1.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=2769.topic&index=10>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Question for the kitties</span><hr size=1> I leveled a Vah Shir Rogue on Luclin, so I sympathise with your pain. <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/smile.gif ALT=":)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END-->   <br>
<br>
The scorpions are the best bet for newbies, and I would suggest slaughtering every whiptail in sight, sharing with your fellow newbies of course. *stern look* The whiptails and skeletons (grimling skeletons? I don't remember) are going to be your moneymaker. You can do the scorpion shell quest for an okay newbie earring, and the Friendship ring quest for a nice ring. Give four scorpion shells to Dharr, the fisherman who is on the other side of the wall from the Registrar for your earring.<br>
<br>
After that, outside to kill everything in sight. The nusances drop cloth armor, so kill every one of those you can. The skeletal hunters have spears. Kill every one of the little aliens you can find. The black ones drop shade silk ((Shade silk armor is just cool. <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/smile.gif ALT=":)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END-->   Its black!)) and the green ones have money. Ah heck, just kill everything in sight. And do the Ghulam armor quests. They're a pain in the tail, but you won't get better armor for a bit. <br>
<br>
Myself and my partner, a shaman, had about 20 plat by the time we headed into Paludal at level 9. He had more than me, so I'm not sure what I was doing wrong. <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/smile.gif ALT=":)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END-->   Its not easy, but its doable. Out in Paludal, the recondite bandits drop bronze brigandine which sells for a few plat each piece. <br>
<br>
The Vah Shir newbie area is designed with quests, rather than money. If you do the quests, you'll get a decent outfit, and be able to spend your few plat on spells. <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/smile.gif ALT=":)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END-->    <br>
<br>
Edit: Forgot the whisperling quest. /bonk self. Its a quest for a shield, which I think is usable by every Vah Shir class. Not sure... Remember that glowy rock? There's a whisperling there.... I'd tell you how to do it, but where's the fun in that? <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START ;) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/wink.gif ALT=";)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END-->  <p></p><i>Edited by: <A HREF=http://pub94.ezboard.com/uscorchedscales.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Scorchedscales</A> at: 9/24/02 10:03:16 am<br></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=d1c3b5><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub94.ezboard.com/ulethecerulre.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Lethe Cerulre</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Siokitty Silvermoon <br>Krazy Kitty</span><br>  Posts: 173<br> <font color=#A62A2A>(9/24/02 11:04:51 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub94.ezboard.com/ffirionaviefrm1.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=2769.topic&index=11>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Question for the kitties</span><hr size=1> I get upset when people choose to be a Vah Shir and then leave Luclin too soon.  It really irks me.  I dealt with being a poor Shaman... I know how it goes... it's rough indeed... but if you don't like it... don't do it... don't keep yourself stuck where you don't want to be in a character you don't like because of the way they set up the race to be.  I absolutely love the way that the Vah Shir work and as a newbie I was willing to go out and kill as many things as I had to to get the money I needed for spells.  Being a Vah Shir is not about money... in the beginning it's about quests that teach you things about your class and race and prep you for the Sonic Bane quest.  Don't like that?  Don't play a Vah.  Not meaning to sound bitchy... I'm just tired of hearing it over and over again.<br>
<br>
By the time you are 30 you can safely get in and out of Paludal (that means the fiends aren't bugging you anymore).  By then go out and hunt in money places if you are all about the money.  My character is only 39 now and she would be higher if I didn't have to do skill things and stuff to get enough cash to buy my Blue Diamond... specifically for my brewing... which goes back to the Sonic Bane quests.  Everything I do with my character all goes back to the Vah Shir.  My excitement for all the Vah Shir stuff is the only thing that has kept be from rerolling into a Dark Elf.<br>
<br>
Just my 2 cp... <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=d1c3b5><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub94.ezboard.com/uthevolcanogod.showPublicProfile?language=EN>thevolcanogod</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br>  Posts: 72<br> <font color=#A62A2A>(9/24/02 1:50:38 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub94.ezboard.com/ffirionaviefrm1.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=2769.topic&index=12>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Question for the kitties</span><hr size=1> Hmm, I missed the part in the SoL guide that said (P.S - only play a Vah Shir if you enjoy being completely isolated until lvl12 and poor until lvl30 unless you travel to other areas to hunt 'cause you know, we just decided that that's how the class is so you should enjoy it and STFU)<br>
<br>
I guess this comes down to the whole, &quot;I play my Vah my way and you play yours your way.&quot; Seems like I hear this a lot but still see a lot of comments to the effect of &quot;It really pisses me off that you do blah,blah with your toon. That's not the right way. MY way is the RIGHT way. And since I said it first, if you don't like MY way, please reroll 'cause you are playing your toon wrong.&quot;<br>
<br>
Anyways, the original poster asked about the money situation for new Vah Shir. We answered him. Sorry you don't like hearing the truth repeated over and over. Or did you just forget to go back and read what the original poster was asking about?<br>
Vulrath <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=d1c3b5><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub94.ezboard.com/umithlin.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Mithlin</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br>  Posts: 30<br> <font color=#A62A2A>(9/24/02 2:41:20 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub94.ezboard.com/ffirionaviefrm1.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=2769.topic&index=13>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Question for the kitties</span><hr size=1> The area around Shar Vahl is designed with quests in mind.  Even some of the shaman spells can be quested.  If you do that whisperling quest mentioned above, the reward in several steps are shaman spells.  Though when I did it back in January, some were broken and gave the wrong spell.<br>
<br>
Other ways to make money:<br>
<br>
HQ rockhopper hides - can be made into tailored backpacks, and you can get them as low as level 1 off needle clawed hoppers in Shadeweaver's Thicket<br>
Perfect Owlbear Pelts - regularly sell for up to 200pp<br>
Chitterling barbs - Used by tinkerers, sells for 25-75pp<br>
Quests - The padded armor quest, the button girl quest, and so on, sometimes netting you up to severalpp in coin and items.<br>
<br>
And as to being isolated...  It is possible to get a Vah Shir off the moon at level 1, without any assistance, and without training anybody.  I personally disagree with doing it aside from travel, but it is possible.<br>
<br>
